    Work with mutable and partial data in Azure Cache for Redis - Summary

    »

    1. What happens if a command in a Redis transaction fails?

      If a command is queued with incorrect syntax, the transaction will be automatically discarded if you try to execute it. If a command fails during execution, the transaction will complete as normal.

      Commands prior to the failing command will still be executed, but those after the failing command will not be.

      The entire transaction will be rolled back.

      The connection will be aborted.


    2. Which of the following is a Redis command for managing data expiration?

      DEL

      DISCARD

      TIMEOUT

      EXPIRE


    3. Your Redis cache is configured with the volatile-ttl eviction policy. If it runs out of memory and you try to insert a new key, which existing key is removed?

      The least recently used key.

      A random key.

      The key that would next expire.

      A random key, selected from keys that have been configured to expire.
